title: For Sale/Trade:  Rossi .44 Magnum 2.5" bbl Revolver!
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is my almost new Rossi .44 Magnum revolver, model R44102. It is a 5 shot .44 Magnum with a 2.5 inch barrel, blue. This awesome revolver comes stock with a fiber optic front site and great rubber grip that has to be felt to be believed. 

This gun has only had 5 shots fired through it, ever, and those were .44 special, not magnums, so it is very nearly brand new. 44 special are very controllable in this small but sturdy package. I would imagine full magnums might be a bit snappy, but specials are pretty awesome. The five rounds I fired were just to test funcionality. While it's a cool gun, it doesn't fit my needs, so I'm looking to sell or trade. As far as I know, you won't find many of these in Massachusetts.

I was able to conceal this fairly well, it's hefty but not crazy heavy, and was very accurate at 15 yards, surprisingly so. The fiber optic front site is very handy.

Included is the original cardboard box, all paperwork it came with, 95 rounds of Blazer hollowpoints, 20 rounds of Hornady Critical Defense 165 gr FTX, and one speed loader. BAM!

I am looking to trade this for a Ruger SR9 full size, first. I might be willing to trade for other full size 9mm semi autos, or possibly sell outright for $450 but trade for SR9 is first option. On eFA10, within reasonable distance of Millbury/Worcester/Uxbridge. 

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Spanish Civil War M91/30
postcontent:
I've got a Mosin from the Spanish Civil War, a 1936 Tula model. It's definitely an SCW Mosin, with the post sight, rough stock, wire sling hanger, and a faint MP8 mark. Numbers do not match, but on SCW's, none of them do. The bore looks great, but I havent shot or cleaned it. 

If you dont know the significance of an SCW Mosin, don't waste either of our time with responses like "I can buy that at Bubbas gun shop for $150!". No, not one like this you can't. Or maybe you can and Bubba is an idiot, in which case I'm buying his too. This rifle is rated an 8/10 on rarity, so you might not see another one locally for quite a while. I know in years of Mosin collecting, this is the first i've seen. Pictures upon request!

I might be interested in a trade, but i've got selective interests. If you've got a PPS-43C or something like that we can definitely make a trade - I like old Soviet stuff, or remakes of said. This is a bit random, but I'd also love an old project DJ-5 postal jeep...they usually sell for around this price in unrestored condition. But, I'm open to other things, so let me know what you've got!
